    <item>
      <title>Re: Can Warrior's Solo?</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=warriorbalance&amp;message.id=19987#M19987</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;from levels 1-6 most  newbie zones&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;for levels 6-10 most  2ndary newbiezones , rathe mountains , areas  of innothule swamp , front  part of guk ,  crushbone etc .&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;from 10 - 15 2ndary  newbie zones .&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;15-20 much  better  grouping  , the soloing locations continue to be 2ndary  newbie zones . and light  blue mobs vs full blue mobs . you  can handle more , but  mobs are less exp each . try  front of najena also&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;20-30 soloing  is not really  an ption ,  you are now between  blues  and light blues . i did some ghouls in unrest , and upper guk deep  near the lower guk zone line&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;30-35 soloing  gets better  .  permafrost  was my  favorite ,  sol A , ,  guk top , especially  near  live side zone in .&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;35-40 soloing  wanes again  as you  get  between  lightblues and greens in power  . need to  start  twinking  to  solo  half effectively . i did kedge ,  but i had a fishbone earring . &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;40-50 front  of guk bottom , parts of nurga , sol B  front  with  shrink (its important  to  be fully  shrunk ,  lots of newbs will stand at  zone in , which  you  will  use  to  split  or  heal outside)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;50-60 you are again  between light  blues and greens . need a snare whip . burning  woods near the chardok zone . if you have ample invis . 58-60 i did alot of KC , with a  fungi tunic and bloodpoints .&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;equipment priorities&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;magic weapon (anything that lets you  hit a wisp) don't  forget  magic boots , magic shield , magic shoulders if you are a large race using slam .&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;haste item . mitheral 2 hander is better  than  exe axe but  worse than  the axe from the hole . remember  from  1-20  there is a damage cap so you  probably  would want  to use 1handers  before 2 handers .&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;regen  or lifetap items . fungi tunic , bloodpoints , stun whips from  paw (these help your healing  by  keeping mobs stunned) ,bandaid dagger from 4th floor in ToFS&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;snare items , silken  whip of ensnare . kunzar  k'juch , stun whips from paw ,  ykesha swords . anything that  stuns or snares .&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;slow weaps , truncheon of doom , the claw from dragon necropolis . try not  to use the spear from NToV , its very  high resist  compared to the others and a significantly  worse slow .&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;</description>
