      <title>Re: Can Warrior's Solo?</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=warriorbalance&amp;message.id=19936#M19936</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;I can solo just fine. I have a cleric I box though, so ussually do not do it, unless I am scared my cleric could get killed. She don't have very good gear.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;I can solo anything I can tank that a cleric would be able to keep up with Cheal easily enough............Providing certain circumstance's are made.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;First of all, has to be an area where I can run around and not get a ton of adds (there are place's). I don't have to be able to run around in a huge area, just need to be able to run enough to keep from getting hit much.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;A combination of Healing potions, and discs.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;What I do, is I just pull as normal. Then after I have gone down in health far enough, I will use the heal over time potions. If I do not last long enough before needing another shot (easy to figure out). I just run the mob around for a few, till I can hit the potion again. If my HP is really hurting, I might keep running till I am almost 100% before engaging again. Rinse and repeat. Bassically a combination of kiting (Without doing damage), and tanking. Using Discs like Furious on Named mob's (For example if doin' WOS), and Bandalier effectively *(To slow, snare, etc.). Discs pretty much suck for most part though, cuz of refresh time, so do not count on them.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This day and age, I do not have much to complain about with my class. I think there is some noticeable class balance issue's between the tanks, but I generally do not have as much to complain about as I used to.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
